Post church thoughts: Forgiveness. Don't look at life through problems. Being defensive puts up a "fence" blinding your vision. Not forgiving others puts you into a mental prison. The world isn't me versus them. When you are defensive, you are projecting on others your battle with yourself. Cancel unforgiveness, bitterness, and defensiveness.

🍤🍙 Shrimp & Crispy Rice

Measurements:
Mix until dissolved 3tbs vinegar, 1tbs sugar, 1tsp salt
1tbs Toasted Sesame Seed Oil
Freeze covered rice for 15-30 (or refrigerate at least an hour)
Deep fry in oil at 365 degree 
Diced shrimp, salt, ground pepper, cayenne, minced garlic
Nori Komi Furikake seasoning
